<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[191,1440,1866,1927]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,1866,1892]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is chosen for the prominent curved crest on the elytral declivity. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="2020" box="[221,344,1900,1927]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus">
<emphasis box="[221,239,1900,1926]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[252,344,1901,1926]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but smaller, hence the diminutive form of the name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
